@node "Createnewproject" "Create New Project"

 This  option  let  you  create a new Bug Reporter raport description file,
 with  all  specific  datas  for  a new project.  This is the key option to
 start   a   new   project.    When  you  select  this  menu  item,  a  new
 @{"Create New Project" link "Createnewprojwin" 0} window  will appear.  After entering all required datas
 and  clicking on OK, you'll be asked for deleting of all existing reports.
 You can choose "Yes", which will delete them, or "No" to let them stay.
 Then the program will return to the main window.
@endnode

@node "modifycurrentproject" "Modify Current Project"

 Selecting  this  menu item will open a @{"Modify Current Project" link "Createnewprojwin" 0} window, with
 all  gadgets  initialized  to  default  values or, if you already loaded a
 report  file, to values defined in that file.  After changing all required
 options  and clicking on OK, program will ask for deleting of all existing
 reports.   You  can  choose  "Yes", which will delete them, or "No" to let
 them  stay.   If  you  are only making changes and you don't want to loose
 already  entered  raports,  please  click  on "No".  Then the program will
 return to the main window.
@endnode

@node "deletefixedbugs" "Delete Fixed Bugs"

 This menu let you delete all reports marked as FIXED or DONE.  This option
 is  very useful for clearing report file from fixed bugs - leaves only the
 interesting ones - not fixed.  Firstly, you'll be asked for confirmation.
 REMEMBER: You can't undo this operation! Deleted reports will be lost!
@endnode

@node "meregeotherfile" "Merge with other bug file"

 This is a very useful option, especially for maintaining big projects with
 a lot of betatesters and a lot of report files.  After selecting this menu
 item,  a  file  requester  will appear.  After selecting the file to merge
 with  primary  report  file, the program will add it at the end of current
 file.   If  there  is  no previously loaded report file, the selected file
 will become the primary.

 PLEASE NOTE: The main project description is taken from the primary file -
 the  project  description from other, merged files will not be used except
 Betatesters field.
@endnode

@node "sendbyemail" "Send Bug Report by E-Mail"

 When  selecting  this menu Bug Reporter will try to send current bug list
 to  email  address,  given in @{"Create or Modify Project" link "Createnewproject" 0} window, using SMTP
 host, if available.  This operation  will  require  one  of TCP/IP stacks
 available  for  Amigas, running in the background (tested with AmiTCP and
 Miami).
@endnode

@node "sortreports" "Sort Reports"

 This option lets you sort reports with selected criteria.  You can choose
 between  sorting  by  Priority,  Type and Date.  All bug reports are then
 also  internally  sorted by type (if sorting by priority was selected) or
 by priority (if sorting by type was selected).
@endnode

