@node "Notes" "General notes"
  Here is a short description how to work with Bug Reporter.

Lets say, you are going to develop an utility or a game.  First, you should
create  a  project  and  enter  all required datas.  If you plan to receive
reports   via  InterNet,  you  need  to  supply  required  informations  in
appriopriate  fields.   Now,  after creating the first beta version of your
program,  you  should give it to every betatester, together with Betatester
BugReporter - a version created especially for them.  They can send reports
directly  over the Internet using Bug Reporter, or save reports and use one
of  their favourite mail programs to e-mail them to you - the developer (or
they can even use the post office...;).  After merging all received reports
together,  you  can  start fixing bugs.  Several hours, days, weeks or even
months  later,  when you are ready, you should send back the report file to
betatesters - you can put there explanations or additional informations for
them  about  each  bug  reported and not fixed.  After a few such turns you
should hopefully get a final, release version of your program.  Now you can
let users of this final version test it and find some more bugs :)

Good luck...
@endnode

